parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Buckle Failure and Recall Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to accidents or injuries due to the inability to properly secure the occupant. The recall issues and unavailability of parts can cause frustration and delay in getting the problem resolved.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is cracked and jammed
the seat belt buckle is hard to buckle
the seat belt buckle has broken again after being replaced under recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden separation of the tire tread can cause the vehicle to jerk or lose control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or pulls to one side
damage to surrounding components such as wheels or body panels.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wheel Well or Body Panel Damage due to Tire Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The damage to the wheel well or body panels can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to further safety issues or costly repairs.
symptoms: visible signs of damage or deformation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked engine head can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on high-speed roads.
symptoms: the engine makes a loud knocking or tapping noise
white smoke or steam comes from the exhaust pipe
the engine stalls or shuts down.
